      <h2>Radiant Conditioning for Commercial Buildings</h2>
      <p>
        Our hydronic radiant ceiling panel system delivers heating and cooling for commercial environments — offices, retail spaces, medical facilities, and aged care — with significant advantages over conventional HVAC.
      </p>
      <p>
        Rather than forcing heated or cooled air through ducts, radiant panels transfer energy directly to occupants and surfaces. The result is <strong>more uniform comfort, better air quality, and lower operating costs</strong>.
      </p>

      <h2>Why Radiant for Commercial?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>No air movement</strong> — eliminates dust circulation, reduces allergens, and creates a quieter working environment</li>
        <li><strong>Zone control</strong> — individual areas can be heated or cooled independently, avoiding the waste of conditioning unoccupied spaces</li>
        <li><strong>Lower running costs</strong> — operates at roughly one-third the cost of conventional ducted systems</li>
        <li><strong>Reduced maintenance</strong> — no filters, fans, or ductwork to service</li>
        <li><strong>Modular installation</strong> — panels fit standard 600 × 1200mm ceiling grids, simplifying installation in new builds and retrofits</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Powered by Renewable Energy</h2>
      <p>
        When paired with our polyvalent heat pump and commercial solar system, hydronic conditioning can run primarily on renewable energy — significantly reducing your building's carbon footprint and operating costs.
      </p>

